cross North America. Regions like the “South”, the “Inland North”, and the “Northeast Corridor” (we’re not going to get into the specifics of where exactly these are, but you probably have good enough ideas in your head) seem to resist this merger most strongly. Thus, if you exhibit this merger, it’s likely that you’re from one of these regions (or linguistically influenced in some way by people/media from there).%0a%3c %0a%3c But how can we figure out someone’s location with this information? There are many other vowel mergers and various pieces of phonetic / lexical information like the Don-Dawn merger, the Southern Vowel Shift, Pin-Pen merger, Dew-Do merger (these are ones related to the “south” in specific, more can be found at en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phonological_history_of_English).%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c TLDR: language changes SO often and that’s SO COOL %0a%3c %0a%3c Resources used:%0a%3c www.nytimes.com/interactive/2014/upshot/dialect-quiz-map.html%0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phonological_history_of_English%0a%3c https://www.ling.upenn.edu/phono_atlas/home.html%0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cot%25E2%2580%2593caught_merger%0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sound_change%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.F